You may all be aware of the lvl 12 necromancer NPC who wonders Qeynos Hills at night, Tovax Vamar.<br>
I got a report from a scout that Tovax was seen wondering far FAR from his usual path.<br>
Well, after following up reports of green mist in Felwith (which turned up to be false), i decided to make Qhills my next stop. Upon arival, it was dead on 12pm, which is when Tovax spawns by the guard tower. I announced that he was my camp, and keeping my distance so he wouldnt attack, I followed him. <br>
Sure enough, he strayed a long way from his usual route. Almost to the ruins, Tovax stopped, dropped a note, and ran. I grabbed the note and took off after him. He then shouted &quot;Oh No! S'garr will have my head for loosing that note!&quot;<br>
S'garr, as we know, is the leader of the Bloodsabres, an important faction in this War.<br>
The note read rougly as follows, although I'll have to take a SS of it and report word for word.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dear Opal, we have ready our forces within the Sewers of Qeynos, waiting on the command to attack. We suffer from the interference of the Temple of Life (i think thats what it said) and greatly need your assistance in this matter. From S'ragg.&quot;<br>
<br>
Prety damn juicy Huh?!?<br>
So I checked Opal out on the web, and guess what. There are two. Both very powerful, one is the leader of the necromancer guild in NFP, and the other is the leader of the enchanter guild in WFP <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Now let me ask you...which Opal from the letter was being reffered to? <br>
